       isdatadescriptor.__code__.co_name.__eq__,
       ["isdatadescriptor"],
       true,
       "inspect.isdatadescriptor.__code__.co_name.__eq__('isdatadescriptor') == True — isdatadescriptor is a pure-Python function in Lib/inspect.py that returns True if the object is a data descriptor (defines both __get__ and __set__ or __delete__); its code object's co_name stores the name from the def statement which is 'isdatadescriptor' (16 chars); str.__eq__('isdatadescriptor') returns True; no prior inspect spec checks isdatadescriptor.__code__.co_name via inspmore75; new to extra75"]
